  "texts": [
    "One key issue is the traceable personal information in these letters, which, if published, would violate the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).",
    "Additionally, ethical concerns stem from the potential impact that disclosing such information might have on relatives or third parties involved.",
    "This is further complicated by past agreements with donors who imposed restrictions on their archives and the possible application of the author's rights to the original texts [Keijzer et al., 2022].",
    "By considering ethics as one important part of data publication, CARE has partially been accounted for in this case.",
    "To take just one example, Dutch legislation has not specified in detail how to deal with these issues."
  ],
